{"type":"step-attempt","step":"cross-boundary-invariants","sessionId":"ef016484-01f4-4c1e-91c5-2589ae7612ff","outcome":{"verdict":"approved","findingsPath":"specrunner/changes/achieved-assurance-completeness/cross-boundary-invariants-result-001.md","error":null,"toolResult":{"ok":true,"approved":true,"findings":[],"observations":[{"severity":"low","file":"src/core/archive/achieved-assurance.ts","title":"testDerivation absent when readFileAtCommit missing from runtime, even in testDerivation-only floor","rationale":"P3 runtime method check requires readFileAtCommit for BOTH testDerivation and biteEvidence, even though testDerivation does not call runTestsAtCommit. Any runtime without readFileAtCommit fails-closed at P3. In production, both LocalRuntime and ManagedRuntime implement it; all existing fail-closed fakes remain fail-closed at a different (earlier) exit point. Intentional per design.","line":175},{"severity":"low","file":"src/core/runtime/local.ts","title":"Suffix match can produce false-positive candidates when one slug is a proper suffix of another archived slug","rationale":"endsWith('-' + pathSuffix) can hit slug S when archived slug X ends with '-S' (e.g. S='slug', X='my-slug'). Multiple matches → unavailable (fail-closed). Acknowledged in design Risk section; slug naming convention makes collision practically impossible.","line":1075},{"severity":"low","file":"src/core/runtime/__tests__/bite-evidence-e2e-gate.test.ts","title":"TC-010 (floor) e2e test uses candidateOid as finalHeadOid, exercising active-path resolution only","rationale":"Production flow uses archiveSha (post-git-mv) exercising the '-' suffix path. The e2e test uses candidateOid (pre-archive) exercising the '/' suffix path. The '-' suffix path is covered by TC-008 unit test with mock spawn but not by a full integration test through runMergeThenArchive.","line":222},{"severity":"low","file":"src/core/archive/achieved-assurance.ts","title":"testDerivation=frozen can be present in achieved while biteEvidence is absent","rationale":"testDerivation is set before the biteEvidence section runs. Subsequent biteEvidence failure (type gate, base-red unavailable, HEAD-red) does not clear testDerivation. This is correct and intended (TC-025), but future consumers of the achieved object must not assume testDerivation implies biteEvidence.","line":324},{"severity":"low","file":"src/core/archive/achieved-assurance.ts","title":"runTestsAtCommit(finalHeadOid) assumes git mv in archive commit does not affect test outcomes","rationale":"The archive commit moves specrunner/changes/<slug>/ but not src/. materializedTestFiles are in src/tests/ (excluded from git mv by isExcludedPath). The invariant holds by archive-change-folder.ts design but is not enforced at the deriveAchievedAssurance call site.","line":389}]},"followUpAttempts":0,"transientRetryAttempts":0,"addedTurns":{"reportRetry":0,"postWork":0,"outputRepair":0}},"startedAt":"2026-07-18T01:05:48.092Z","endedAt":"2026-07-18T01:17:05.847Z"}
